On Saturday, firefighters used a respite from strong winds to drop fire retardant in a bid to strengthen firebreaks.But officials warned that winds of up to 70mph (112km/h) are expected over the coming days, meaning fires could spread quickly and unexpectedly."Winds are already blowing. They are going to blow for the next three days. Your house can be rebuilt but you can't bring your life back," said Los Angeles County fire chief Daryl Osby.
                
                
                
                
                
